features: ▌ Monochrome Laser Printer: not color Printer. One-Sided scanning only.▌ The Brother DCP-L2550DW 3-in-1 Laser All-in-One is the ideal choice for the busy home or small office looking for a fast, reliable multi-function copier.

〓 One-Sided scanning only 〓 An all-in-one design makes it a great choice for space-conscious offices as it fits printing, scanning, and copying within a single unit. Also, the printing capabilities are very good with a max resolution of 2400 x 600 dpi and print speeds of up to 36 ppm.
The printer can also work with documents up to 8.5 x 14" in size using the 250-sheet input tray or one-sheet manual feed slot.

Scanning and copying is made possible through the inclusion of an 8.5 x 11.7" flatbed and a 50-sheet ADF. Also, an optical resolution of 1200 x 1200 dpi for the flatbed and 600 dpi for the ADF ensure that scans are detailed and sharp. For operation, the DCP-L2550DWA has a two-line monochrome LCD, which enables various direct printing and scanning options.
Additionally, it features Wi-Fi connectivity, alongside standard USB 2.0 and Ethernet, for completely wireless operation and support for direct printing from mobile devices.
body.description: Feature Rich. Budget Minded. Laser Focused. The Brother DCP-L2550DWA is the ideal choice for the busy home or small office looking for a fast, reliable multi-function copier. This multiple-use copier includes a 50-sheet automatic document feeder, which allows multi-page copying and scanning, and class-leading print speeds of up to 36 pages per minute for increased efficiency. This printer and copier has a Wi-Fi connection, which allows printing from wireless devices including desktops, smartphones, laptops, and tablets. For those who prefer hardwire connections, there s an Ethernet interface for sharing with multiple users on your network. You can also connect locally to a single computer via USB interface. The 250-sheet paper tray handles letter- and legal-sized paper, designed to improve office efficiency. Automatic duplex (2-sided) printing also saves paper and creates professional-looking documents for presentations, newsletters, and other common office needs. Brother genuine high-yield replacement cartridges deliver up to twice the standard print volume, which helps to reduce operational costs.3-in-1 Laser All-in-OneB/W Laser TechnologyMonochrome print speeds of up to 32 pages per minute* with maximum duty cycle of 15,000 pages a month.USB, Wireless12.5"H x 16.1"W x 15.7"D250-sheet paper capacity up to legal (8.5"x14") sized paperStandard Memory: 128MBAutomatic duplexing (two sided printing)Two line mono display2400 x 1200 DPI color scanningUses Brother TN-730, TN-760 , DR730 cartridgesConnect and print your way. Works with Alexa Print for voice activated printing or choose from versatile connection options with built-in wireless or connect locally to a single computer via its USB interface.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Reliable and clean copies
reviews.reviewText: I love this printer! It is easy to set up. It is reliable. The toner is inexpensive. It is everything I wanted for my small business in contrast to the ink printers I have had that clog up and stop working after a year and can't be fixed. I don't miss color. When I need it, I'll go to staples.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Was very difficult to download software, and refuses to work with wi-fi.
reviews.reviewText: I've had Brother printers for years, and this is the only disappointment I've had. It works fine with a USB cable but will not work with wi-fi. I usually set everything up myself, but I spent $100 to get this one ready to go and the next day had the same wi-fi- problems. I will probably return it.
